      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PETIT CHERIE (1) flew the lids from out wide with a slick early split but ran over at the finish when a narrow fourth (26.05) over 460m at Warragul. Has ability and can bounce back. FOCUS FRANKY (2) was an effortless winner two back when prominent throughout then got further back last time but came home hard into second and beaten 2.75 lengths at Warragul (26.39). Form from her last run is proving to be solid. Will give a great sight again. ESCAPING BINDI (8) started big odds but ran one of the quickest times of the card with a one length win (24.59) at Sale latest. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in her latest win. Sure to be thereabouts. BLINKED (3) can play a role in the finish without surprising.",
